                    <span>Thank you for your kind reviews. I hope you have as much fun working with SQL Server as I do. If you're a SQL Server DBA, developer, or architect, I have two suggestions; 
<br />
<br />First, join your local Profession Association for SQL Server (SQLPASS.org) chapter. The SQL Server community is a growing and positive group. 
<br />
<br />Second, after you've read my book, continue learning. I highly recommend these books: 
<br />
<br />* Inside SQL Server by Kalen Delany 
<br />* Advanced Transact-SQL by Itzik Ben-Gan & Tom Moreau
<br />* Hitchhiker's Guide to Reporting Services by Bill Vaughn 
<br />* Microsoft SQL Server 2005 New Features by Michael Otey 
<br />
<br />It's critical that the book is accurate and the errata page on the book's website (www.sqlserverbible.com) keeps everyone honest. There are a handfull known errors: 4 screen shots mis-captioned, 1 screen shot mis-cropped, 1 table with transposed cells, and 1 mis-wording. If you discover any other errors please write to me. 
<br />
<br />I hope to meet you at a SQL PASS Summit. 
<br />
<br />may all your queries run swift and true, 
<br />-Paul Nielsen, SQL Server MVP 
<br />
<br />p.s. I would have preferred to not rate my own book, but the Rating column has a NOT NULL constraint.</span>
                  
